x10.matrix

Class Vector

  • x10.matrix.Vector
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    x10.lang.Any

    public class Vector
implements x10.lang. Fun_0_1<x10.lang.Int,x10.lang.Double>
    Declaration: Vector implements (x10.lang.Int)=>x10.lang.Double.
    Class Vector uses an M * 1 array as data staorage)

 
     This implemnetation has a dense, single-place representation.

 
     Methods include 
 
     1) product of two vectors: Mx1
1xM,
 
     2) product of vector and a scalar: Mx1
1,
 
     3) product of a scalar and a vector: 1
1xM,
 
     4) addition of two vectors: Mx1 + Mx1,
 
     5) substraction between two vectors: Mx1 - Mx1,
 
     6) addition of a vector and a scalar: Mx1 + 1,
 
     7) substraction of a scalar from a vector: Mx1 - 1,
 
     8) inverse of a vector: Mx1
 
     9) norm of a vector: Mx1

         This implemnetation has a dense, single-place representation.

 
         Methods include 
 
         1) product of two vectors: Mx1

         2) product of vector and a scalar: Mx1
1,
 
         3) product of a scalar and a vector: 1
1xM,

         5) substraction between two vectors: Mx1 - Mx1,
 
         6) addition of a vector and a scalar: Mx1 + 1,
 
         7) substraction of a scalar from a vector: Mx1 - 1,
